In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook for ~{10%minutes}.

Drain @Black Beans{1%unit}.

Once rice has cooked 10 minutes, stir in drained black beans; cover and cook until rice is tender, ~{5-8%minutes} more.

While rice and beans cook, wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}. Trim and discard root end from @Baby Lettuce{1%unit}; thinly slice half the lettuce (all for 4 servings) crosswise into ribbons. Dice @Tomato{1%unit} into ¼-inch pieces; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Ground Turkey{10%ounce}, scallion whites, garlic, @Cumin{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper.

Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> Swap in beef for turkey if preferred.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Sour Cream{1.5%tablespoon} and scallion greens. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice and beans with a #fork{}; taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice and beans and beef mixture between shallow #bowls{} in separate sections. Top everything with sliced lettuce, tomato, and scallion crema. Serve.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.